creator: Gladys Cromwell
description:
LibriVox volunteers bring you 17 recordings of Star Song by Gladys Cromwell (1885 - 1919). This was the Weekly Poetry project for May 4th, 2014. Read in English by ashleighjane; Amanda Vickery; David Lawrence; Ernst Pattynama; Ezwa; fshort; Garth Burton; Glenn O'Brien; Jason Mills; JGHenry; Jeanie; Lee Ann Howlett; Leonard Wilson; Peregrinus Tyß; Ruth Golding; ravenotation. Gladys Cromwell was a fine young poet who, with her twin sister, sadly ended her own life after experiencing the horrors of the First World War while serving with the Red Cross in France. For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (10MB)
